This paper proposes a new method for variational inference in autoencoders, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of deep learning. The paper specifically focuses on importance weighted variational inference, which is a technique used in probabilistic modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as autoencoders are commonly used in these fields. The paper also introduces a hierarchical structure to induce correlation, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
